input.command:
coop-send agent2 --type "SPEC" --files "llama-index-core/llama_index/core/evaluation/retrieval/metrics.py" --spec "In NDCG.compute(), the IDCG calculation must iterate over the number of EXPECTED relevant documents, not min(len(retrieved_ids), len(expected_ids)). Replace:
    ideal_length = min(len(retrieved_ids), len(expected_ids))
    idcg = sum(
        discounted_gain(rel=True, i=i, mode=mode)
        for i in range(1, ideal_length + 1)
    )
with:
    idcg = sum(
        discounted_gain(rel=True, i=i, mode=mode)
        for i in range(1, len(expected_ids) + 1)
    )
Rationale: standard NDCG defines IDCG as the DCG of the ideal ranking of all relevant (expected) documents, regardless of how many docs were retrieved. Clamping to len(retrieved_ids) under-counts IDCG when fewer docs are retrieved than are truly relevant, inflating the NDCG score. Please preserve this iteration bound (len(expected_ids)) when integrating your relevance_scores parameter into the idcg sum." --note "Exact replacement for the ideal_length/idcg block in NDCG.compute()"

